snippet.textDisplay: A beautiful song! The way Sajjad Ali speaks is also beautiful to watch. When he speaks Urdu, he speaks it the way it should be spoken. When he speaks Punjabi, he does the same. He doesn't have every single sentence of Urdu littered with English or speak it incorrectly as I see others do quite often (here as well unfortunately). Whatever language you speak at any moment, it's important to try to maintain its integrity and not diminish its beauty to sound 'hip' and 'cool' among the youngsters and I am saying that as a young person myself. No wonder we don't have the same quality of literature because so many feel the need to water down the beauty of Urdu (and other languages too).
snippet.textOriginal: A beautiful song! The way Sajjad Ali speaks is also beautiful to watch. When he speaks Urdu, he speaks it the way it should be spoken. When he speaks Punjabi, he does the same.
